### Measure Async Operation Performance in Payload CMS Access Checks

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/ACCESS-CONTROL-ADVANCED.md

This asynchronous TypeScript access function demonstrates how to measure the execution time of an external API call within a Payload CMS access check. It logs the duration of the `fetch` operation, providing insight into potential performance bottlenecks introduced by asynchronous logic.

```typescript
export const timedAsyncAccess: Access = async ({ req }) => {
  const start = Date.now()

  const result = await fetch('https://auth-service.example.com/validate', {
    headers: { userId: req.user?.id }
  })

  console.log(`Access check took ${Date.now() - start}ms`)

  return result.ok
}
```

