### Perform Direct Database Update Operation in Payload (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/performance/overview.mdx

This TypeScript snippet demonstrates how to use `payload.db.updateOne` to directly update a document in the database. This method bypasses Payload's hooks and validations, offering significant performance improvements for operations like updates, especially when the returned document is not immediately needed.

```ts
await payload.db.updateOne({
  collection: 'posts',
  id: post.id,
  data: {
    title: 'New Title',
  },
})
```

