### Performance Optimization with Limit

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/queries/pagination.mdx

Utilize the `limit` option to optimize query performance, especially when fetching single documents by unique identifiers.

```APIDOC
## Performance Benefits of `limit`

### Description

Setting a `limit` of `1` (or a low number) can significantly improve performance when you expect only a single document to match your query criteria, such as when querying by a unique field like `slug`.

### Method

`find` (Local or REST API)

### Endpoint

N/A (Local API) or `/api/[collection-slug]` (REST API)

### Parameters

#### Query Parameters

- **limit** (number) - Optional - Limits the number of documents returned per page. Set to `1` for single document fetches.

### Request Example (Local API)

```ts
await payload.find({
  collection: 'posts',
  where: {
    slug: {
      equals: 'post-1',
    },
  },
  limit: 1,
})
```

### Response

#### Success Response (200)

Returns a single document or an empty array if no match is found, along with pagination metadata (where `limit` will be `1`).

#### Response Example

```json
{
  "docs": [
    {
      "title": "Post 1",
      "slug": "post-1",
      "createdAt": "2023-01-01T10:00:00.000Z",
      "updatedAt": "2023-01-01T10:00:00.000Z",
      "id": "someId123"
    }
  ],
  "totalDocs": 1,
  "limit": 1,
  "totalPages": 1,
  "page": 1,
  "pagingCounter": 1,
  "hasPrevPage": false,
  "hasNextPage": false,
  "prevPage": null,
  "nextPage": null
}
```
```

