### Checking the Status of a Payload Job (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/jobs-queue/jobs.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to retrieve and inspect the status of a job after it has been queued. By querying the `payload-jobs` collection with the job's ID, you can access properties like `completedAt`, `hasError`, and `taskStatus` to monitor its progress and outcome.

```ts
const job = await payload.jobs.queue({
  task: 'processPayment',
  input: { orderId: '123' },
})

// Later, check the job status
const updatedJob = await payload.findByID({
  collection: 'payload-jobs',
  id: job.id,
})

console.log(updatedJob.completedAt) // When it finished
console.log(updatedJob.hasError) // If it failed
console.log(updatedJob.taskStatus) // Details of each task
```

