### Query Optimization - Indexes

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/queries/overview.mdx

Improve query performance by adding database indexes to frequently queried or sorted fields within your Payload collection configurations. This prevents full document scans, speeding up data retrieval.

```APIDOC
## Query Optimization - Indexes

### Description
Enhance query speed by configuring indexes on fields that are frequently used in 'where' clauses or for sorting. An index allows the database to quickly locate data without scanning entire collections.

### Method
Collection Configuration

### Parameters
#### Field Configuration
- **index** (boolean) - Required - Set to `true` on a field to create a database index for it. Defaults to `false`.

### Request Example
```typescript
// In your collection configuration
{
  name: 'posts',
  fields: [
    {
      name: 'title',
      type: 'text',
      index: true // Add an index to the title field
    },
    // Other fields...
  ]
}
```

### Response
This is a configuration setting and does not have a direct API response, but it impacts the performance of subsequent API queries.
```

