### Perform Direct Database Update Without Returning Document in Payload (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/performance/overview.mdx

This TypeScript example shows how to use `payload.db.updateOne` with the `returning: false` option. Setting `returning: false` prevents the updated document from being fetched and returned, reducing database computation and response size. This option is exclusive to direct-to-db methods.

```ts
await payload.db.updateOne({
  collection: 'posts',
  id: post.id,
  data: { title: 'New Title' },
  returning: false,
})
```

