### Query Optimization - Depth Control

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/queries/overview.mdx

Optimize query performance and response size by limiting the population 'depth' of related documents. This ensures only necessary levels of relationships are fetched, reducing database overhead.

```APIDOC
## Query Optimization - Depth Control

### Description
Control the extent to which related documents are populated when fetching data. Setting a lower `depth` avoids over-fetching unnecessary nested data, improving performance and reducing response payload size.

### Method
`payload.find()` (Local API, also applicable to other APIs where depth can be controlled)

### Parameters
#### Request Body (for `payload.find` options)
- **depth** (number) - Optional - The number of levels to populate relationships. `0` means only IDs are returned for related documents. Defaults to `1`.

### Request Example
```typescript
const posts = await payload.find({
  collection: 'posts',
  where: { /* ... */ },
  depth: 0 // Only return the IDs of related documents
});
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **docs** (array) - An array of documents where related fields are populated up to the specified depth. If `depth: 0`, related fields will only contain the ID.

#### Response Example (depth: 0)
```json
{
  "docs": [
    {
      "id": "postId1",
      "title": "Post Title",
      "author": "authorId123" // Only the ID of the related author
    }
  ],
  "totalDocs": 1,
  "limit": 10,
  "page": 1,
  "totalPages": 1,
  "hasPrevPage": false,
  "hasNextPage": false,
  "pagingCounter": 1
}
```
```

