### Get Cached Payload Instance for Reuse - TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/performance/overview.mdx

Shows how to use the getPayload function to retrieve a cached Payload instance instead of creating new instances unnecessarily. This caching mechanism improves performance by reusing the same instance across the application, reducing initialization overhead and memory usage.

```typescript
import { getPayload } from 'payload'
import config from '@payload-config'

const myFunction = async () => {
  const payload = await getPayload({ config })

  // use payload here
}
```

