### Avoid N+1 Queries in Payload CMS Access Functions (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/ACCESS-CONTROL-ADVANCED.md

Highlights the N+1 query problem that arises when an asynchronous access function performs a database lookup (`findByID`) for each document in a list, leading to poor performance. The efficient solution demonstrates how to return a query constraint directly, allowing the database to filter records at the query level, thereby avoiding multiple individual lookups.

```typescript
// ❌ N+1 Problem: Query per access check
export const n1Access: Access = async ({ req, id }) => {
  // Runs for EACH document in list
  const doc = await req.payload.findByID({ collection: 'docs', id })
  return doc.isPublic
}

```

```typescript
// ✅ Better: Use query constraint to filter at DB level
export const efficientAccess: Access = () => {
  return { isPublic: { equals: true } }
}

```
